author: deepal
msg: W3C provides a “SOAP Version 1.2 Specification Assertions and Test Collection”. They have given set of request messages and expected reply messages. If a SOAP processer replies expected reply messages when it receives given requests that soap processer is said to be SOAP 1.2 complient. In this test suite all the given request messages are sent and replies are compared with expected messages. If those are matched particular test number is passed. That’s the task of this test suite.  And the total implementation done by following students
